social_posts.post_text: I guess the jokes on Alabama, they lost big this time. I got the number one pick blonde hair red lips. 🖤
My new single Goodyears and Good Beers is out everywhere today!!! Thank you to God, my Momma and  everyone who made this possible!

Now I’m dodging potholes in my sun burnt Silverado. Like a heart-broke desperado headed right back to my roots. Something about the way she kissed me told me she loves western Michigan oh but all I brought back with me was some sand in my boots.

GoodYears and Good Beers has been performing well. I just wanted to take the time to thank all of you for streaming my music. I have some big plans for an EP coming I appreciate each and every one of you. (Yes that is me as a child)
Born with a beer in my hand.
Well God made her so I’ll make sure he didn’t waste an angel on me.
Who’s ready for Round two in Grand Rapids Michigan at @sectionlive May 13? Thank you to everyone who came out to the first show to see us and support us. We love you all! See you May 13.
They’re trouble but I’ll tell you right now y’all LONG LIVE COWGIRLS
Bringing back Pythons and Skoal rings see y’all tonight Grand Rapids.
Mommas don’t let your Cowboys grow up to be babies (I meant what I said) -CoJo
I don’t know what you’re waiting on but kinda sounds like me to me.
Somewhere now someone’s out there sipping on some 100 proof and every day a baby’s born with some baby blues, a good ol boys got on his faded boots.
If that neon leaves you lonely baby, I know what you need.
Life lately 🇺🇸

“It’s got a touch of the town where I grew up. Something in it those California girls love. Some people like to make a little fun of the way I talk. It gets slower after three or four cold beers it gets louder when I’m cheering on The Volunteers!!! The man upstairs gets it so I ain’t tryna fix it “
“I’m a hell of a lover, a damn good brother and I wear this heart on my sleeve and that might not mean much to you but it does to me”
I’d have a Friday night crowd in the palm of my hand, bright lights like lightning running through my veins.
We got winners, we got losers…..mmm hmm mmm hmm mmm I love this bar
Busch put beer in camouflage cans and John Deer painted em green and that’s why God made a good ol boy
Now I ain’t no straight and narrow but for you I’d walk the line because you’ve got the only heart like mine.

Was it the cool delta mornings or Jackson nights? Did your interstate dreams turn into a dead-end street? Was it a midnight blanket on a river bank or two names on a Tupelo water tank? Is it somethin' bout a boy back home that your heart still needs? So before you come back like that tell me one thing. Were you missin' Tennessee or me?
I get lost somewhere between you and the neon.
We do things a little different round here.
I never believed in Angels until one Believed in me that night.
If tomorrow I lost it all and everything that I had was gone.
This ain’t my last Rodeo
It’s been a hell of a year.
I wish I could get a buck for every one of those green head ducks I knocked down in that Mississippi mud.

If one day you hate me, say that I’m crazy. Get sick of my bullshit and being my baby. Take an old pipe wrench to my drivers side window. Hang my heart on a barbed wire fence post and leave me half-lit howlin at the moon. Yeah I’m probably going to say I hate you too, but I wouldn’t blame you.
God made a girl his best work of art but he didn’t make no place to go when she breaks your heart. So man made a bar.

I quit my job, let my momma down, broke an angels heart on the way out of town. I pulled my roots from the ground for the hum of wheels on a blacktop, the strum of a strings on the flattop. It’s a neon fever for a small-town dreamer. Tells you everything you have is worth losing damn country music.

It's been a long time
Since the Milky Way, Jupiter and Venus took your breath away
Yeah like you're taking mine
What you say we grab some tailgate underneath the stars
Catch a few fireflies in a moonshine jar
You stole this heart ain’t that the truth. I guess that makes you an outlaw too.
I ain’t the kind to settle down or let myself get wrapped around somebody’s finger but if I had you. Baby sounds like something I’d do.
When you find a good girl keep her because they don’t grow on vines. A man could learn a lot from a man behind the times.
That ain’t my damn to give
He’s a seven million dollar bull rider
It it you heart or mine? Whiskey or wine?
It’s workin on me
Where would I’ve first heard Merle or got the nerve to kiss a green eyed girl? If it wasn’t for trucks.

Now my hearts out of love, I fell out of line 
I swore that I’d never leave again and I lied
It was the weight of the world you setting me free
You can’t sleep alone but you ain’t sleeping with me
It’s been a hell of a year
They said I was nothing but a trouble maker always up to no good. You were the perfect All American girl wouldn’t touch me even if you could.
Something about the way she kissed me tells me she’d love eastern Tennessee but all I brought back with me was sand in my boots.

They say a man is only as good as the woman that he’s got standing beside him. So I’ll thank the good lord every day. Mine is somewhere out there waiting for me to ride in. Boy that’ll be the day, she’s so close I can smell her perfume. I can’t wait to watch her light up the room.

Well, how in the hell can I watch the big game without me having you here to complain? How am I going to do anything now without you here telling me how? I guess I’ll miss the bachelorette well what a shame.

MI/TN
Singer/Songwriter 🎶
